The number can be 0 or more.

A 'plant phenological trait' (PPO:0002000) that is measured by the number of a whole plant's ripe seed cones (PPO:0001052) that have been abscised or removed by an herbivore and/or the number of ripe seed cones on a 'whole plant' (PO:0000003) that have abscised at least one 'mature seed' (PPO:0001024).
The number can be 0 or more and only includes the most recent cone crop.
